TY  - JOUR
T1  - Rethinking Sustained Competitive Advantage from Human Capital
AU  - Campbell, Benjamin A.
AU  - Coff, Russell
AU  - Kryscynski, David
Y1  - 2012/07/01
PY  - 2012
DA  - 2012/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2010.0276
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2010.0276
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 376
EP  - 395
VL  - 37
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The strategy literature often emphasizes firm-specific human capital as a source of competitive advantage based on the assumption that it constrains employee mobility. We first identify three boundary conditions that limit the applicability of this logic. We then offer a more comprehensive framework of human capital?based advantage that explores both demand- and supply-side mobility constraints. The critical insight is that these mobility constraints have more explanatory power than the firm specificity of human capital.
AB  - The strategy literature often emphasizes firm-specific human capital as a source of competitive advantage based on the assumption that it constrains employee mobility. We first identify three boundary conditions that limit the applicability of this logic. We then offer a more comprehensive framework of human capital?based advantage that explores both demand- and supply-side mobility constraints. The critical insight is that these mobility constraints have more explanatory power than the firm specificity of human capital.
SN  - 0363-7425
M3  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2010.0276
UR  - https://doi.org/10.5465/amr.2010.0276
