TY  - JOUR
T1  - Crowdsourcing As a Solution to Distant Search
AU  - Afuah, Allan
AU  - Tucci, Christopher L.
Y1  - 2012/07/01
PY  - 2012
DA  - 2012/07/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2010.0146
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2010.0146
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 355
EP  - 375
VL  - 37
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - We argue that under certain circumstances crowdsourcing transforms distant search into local search, improving the efficiency and effectiveness of problem solving. Under such circumstances a firm may choose to crowdsource problem solving rather than solve the problem internally or contract it to a designated supplier. These circumstances depend on the characteristics of the problem, the knowledge required for the solution, the crowd, and the solutions to be evaluated.
AB  - We argue that under certain circumstances crowdsourcing transforms distant search into local search, improving the efficiency and effectiveness of problem solving. Under such circumstances a firm may choose to crowdsource problem solving rather than solve the problem internally or contract it to a designated supplier. These circumstances depend on the characteristics of the problem, the knowledge required for the solution, the crowd, and the solutions to be evaluated.
